title: For Sale:  First Year Production 1959 Browning High Power Safari 30-06
postcontent: ** Located in Enterprise**  1959 Browning High Power Safari chambered in 30-06. What makes this rifle extremely desirable is: 1. This is the first year these rifles were produced and 2. This particular specimen carries a very low serial number (4xx). These rifles were made by the world famous Belgium Company FN, using their Supreme action. FN is so highly regarded that oodles of firearms makers have used their actions to produce their own firearms, such as Weatherby, Husqvarna, Sako, Colt, H&R, and Sears just to name a few.  The Safari rifles are considered by many as one of the best production rifles ever made. They are a control round fed action rifle with a pre 64 Winchester 70 type trigger system (the best and most reliable trigger system every invented). Scope not included.  It no longer is carried in its original wood stock, but rather a bedded Bell and Carlson synthetic stock that is impervious to humidity, rain and temperature changes. There is no rust or pitting on the metal and the bluing is phenomenal for a rifle of this age. The only blemish to the stock is a small bit of the soft recoil pad is missing at the toe.  All in all, this is a sweet rig selling at a sweet price.  I’m currently not interested in trades. As always, I highly encourage that you do your research and price check to ensure that you’re not getting “bent over” if this rifle interests you.
